  "conclusion": "Two independent reasons the LOS effect is negligible and low-z-weighted. (1) Amplitude: the data cap the coupling at |lambda|<0.058 (Probe 3, 3 sigma, rotation-null inflated), so the per-sightline magnitude modulation is at most ~0.046 mag - a few percent of the ~0.2 mag Pantheon+ per-SN error at every redshift (ratio 0.06-0.15). (2) Geometry: Var(F) ~ f(1-f) L_void/D(z) with L_void~22 Mpc/h (many-cell regime), so even a hypothetical order-unity coupling declines with beam length and is concentrated at z<~0.1. Both independently explain WHY the published timescape SN preference is low-z-driven - a low-z/covariance effect, not a high-z cosmological signal."
